                    <div id="tab-54f3adac3931b" tab-id="tab-4" class="tab-pane">
                     <div class="txt-content"> 
                      <div class="row-wrapper row"></div> 
                      <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 six"> 
                       <h5>Server Synchronized EVM</h5> 
                       <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2229" alt="evm" src="http://metrouni.edu.bd/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/evm1.png" width="350" height="193"> Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering of Metropolitan University recently made a modern Server Synchronize Electronics Voting Machine. This device can send each voting information, time, device location, device power level and other various data to the central server and in a secret number by SMS. It ensures the safety of the information. Moreover this machine has a feature to monitor effectiveness of voting button to ensure device hardware safety and it will also lessen any sort of artifice in voting. If information cannot be sent immediately due to weak mobile signal, this device will store all information in offline mood and send information again when it is connected with the network again. 
                      </div> 
                      <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 six"> 
                       <h5>Drone Development</h5> 
                       <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2228" alt="drone" src="http://metrouni.edu.bd/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/drone1.png" width="350" height="199"> The Department of Electrical &amp; Electronic Engineering of Metropolitan University has successfully made a Drone which can perform particular function. It may mention that the drone was made under the lecturer of Electrical &amp; Electronic Department Syed Rezwanul Haque Nabil who Triggered countries wide by making drone while he was the student of Shahjalal University of Science &amp; Technology. In the meantime the demonstration of this tremendous drone is efficiently completed. Some other extraordinary students of Metropolitan University are also working with this Drone project. However University expects some other new drone project will be completed soon. 
                      </div> 
